Question: What type of cultural arts or entertainment opportunities would you like to see more of in Austin?

Response ID: resp_1087
Response Text: I would like to see more higher level art in Austin. I can mostly only speak to theatre, as that is the community I'm most aligned with. As of right now, there is really only ZACH that is able to produce professional-level theatre in this community. The rest of the low-and-mid-budget organizations do INCREDIBLE work for very little money comparatively. But, organizations are often left going nowhere because everything is getting more expensive at a time where funding is drying up. If we want to support our creative class, particularly actors, we need to be able to grow more mid-to-high paying theatrical opportunities for gig artists and technicians. This is not going to be possible if we squeeze out the currently small companies that want to grow into larger institutions. Many long-time groups are happy with the size they are working at. For our entire community to grow, we need more competition and access to decent-paying art jobs. There are many, many, many universities in the area that bring artists to this community. The lack of work here, tied with the increasing affordability crisis, means that many of them end up going to other markets, perpetuating an intense drain of our creative class.

